We want to estimate the probability that, given a peak with true mass <italic>M<sub>j</sub></italic>, a peak at mass <italic>M<sub>j</sub></italic> is observed in the measured spectrum: more precisely, the probability of observing a mass difference of |<italic>M<sub>j</sub></italic>‚àí<italic>m<sub>j</sub></italic>| or larger. We can compute this probability using the complementary error function ‚Äòerfc‚Äô:
